President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring September 20-26, 2020, as National Small Business Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of small businesses in driving the American economy and creating jobs. The administration has provided significant economic relief to small businesses during the COVID-19 pandemic, including loans and grants. The proclamation also highlights efforts to revitalize economically distressed areas through the designation of Opportunity Zones and the promotion of entrepreneurship among underrepresented groups. The president calls on all Americans to recognize the contributions of small business owners and entrepreneurs to the nation's economy.